<Window xmlns="https://github.com/avaloniaui"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:md="clr-namespace:Markdown.Avalonia;assembly=Markdown.Avalonia"
        xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:Harp.Behavior.Design.ViewModels"
        mc:Ignorable="d" d:DesignWidth="650" d:DesignHeight="350"
        Width="650" Height="350"
        x:Class="Harp.Behavior.Design.Views.About"
        x:DataType="vm:AboutViewModel"
        Icon="/Assets/logo.ico"
        WindowStartupLocation="CenterOwner"
        Title="About">
  <StackPanel Spacing="10" Margin="20">
    <Image HorizontalAlignment="Center"
           Width="400"
           Margin="0,5,5,0"
           Source="/Assets/logo_about.png" />
    <md:MarkdownScrollViewer xml:space="preserve" HorizontalAlignment="Center">
      The Harp Behavior GUI can be used to configure and test Harp Behavior devices. The GUI was developed using [.NET](https://dotnet.microsoft.com/), [AvaloniaUI](https://avaloniaui.net/) with ReactiveUI and makes direct use of the [Bonsai.Harp](https://harp-tech.org/articles/operators.html) package.

      The [Harp](https://harp-tech.org/) project exists to provide interoperability standards and tools for accelerating open collaboration, innovation, and discovery in instrumentation for brain and behavior research.
      
      Harp was created by a group of scientists and engineers at the Champalimaud Foundation, and has since expanded to include members of the Open Ephys Production Site, the Sainsbury Wellcome Centre, NeuroGEARS, and the Allen Institute for Neural Dynamics.
    </md:MarkdownScrollViewer>
    </StackPanel>
</Window>
